---
[floor-framing] Floor Framing (notstarted)
Build the floor deck: rim joists, floor joists, blocking, and subfloor sheathing.
Use pressure-treated lumber for the bottom plate if on a trailer or near grade.
---
[wall-framing] Wall Framing (notstarted)
Frame exterior and interior walls on the deck; raise, plumb, and brace.
Include headers over windows/doors and blocking for cabinets and TV mounts.
-> floor-framing
---
[roof-framing] Roof Framing (notstarted)
Install rafters or trusses, ridge board, and roof sheathing (OSB or plywood).
-> wall-framing
> Shed roof is simplest; gable provides loft space; gambrel maximizes headroom.
